body_html: The ubuntu OS evaluation you're comparing for speed, is that on the same processor? (I.e. is it a dual-boot system?) Otherwise it's not clear from what you've posted that the Win7/ICore5 system you're comparing it to is as capable. MNIST is a simple model, most of the eval runtime is floating point matrix multiply. Is it possible that somehow you're running out of memory and swapping? That could cause a huge slowdown and also prevent you from being able to access another process.
